# Deploy workflow

## Default: local testing

- Run and test changes locally (`npm run dev` or `npm run dev:local`) before any production deploy.
- Do not push to GitHub or suggest Vercel deploy unless the user asks for "live", "deploy", "push to production", or similar.

## Daily check-in (~4 PM)

When the user starts or continues work in a session and local time is **4:00 PM or later** (use their timezone if known; otherwise assume US local), ask once per day:

> Want to take today's changes live on Vercel? (yes / no)

- If **no**: continue local-only; do not push for deploy.
- If **yes**: confirm env vars (`APP_URL`, `DATABASE_URL`, etc.), then push to `main` if there are unpushed commits so Vercel auto-deploys.

## Database

- Production uses **Neon** (`DATABASE_URL`). Do not migrate to Supabase unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Production host

- **Vercel** is production. Netlify is deprecated for this project.
- Guide: `DEPLOY-VERCEL.md`
